'''Robert Cortes''' (born July 28, 1948) is a retired [[United States|American]] [[professional wrestler]] and [[trainer]], known by his ringname '''Bobby Bold Eagle''', who wrestled throughout the United States for the [[National Wrestling Alliance]] and the [[World Wide Wrestling Federation]] during the late 1960s and 1970s.

==Career==
A protege of [[Argentina Rocca]], he made his WWWF debut in September 1968.

In 1981, he held the [[NWA World Junior Heavyweight Championship|NWA]] and [[WWF Junior Heavyweight Championship]]s simultaneously for around three weeks. In late-1989, he was featured in a [[cover story]] for ''[[Newsday]]''.<ref>Friedman, David. "Follow The Bouncing Boys." ''[[Newsday]]''. 27 November 1989 [Nassau and Suffolk Edition]: 4.</ref>

Cortes wrestled throughout the world during his near 15-year career including countries such as [[Guatemala]], [[Mexico]], [[Puerto Rico]], [[Japan]], [[Saudi Arabia]], [[Africa]] and most of [[Europe]]. While in [[Joint Promotions]] in the 1980s, he held the promotion's tag team championship as part of a [[kayfabe]] "brother" tag team with former student Al Bold Eagle.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.oklafan.com/bios/149/profile.html |title=Bios: Al Farat |author= |year=2008 |work=The Oklahoma Fan's Wrestling Resource Center |publisher=OklaFan.com |accessdate=2010-05-23}}</ref> He was also a sometimes ally of [[Shirley Crabtree|Big Daddy]] in his feud with [[Frank Hoy|Wild Angus Campbell]] and wrestled the likes of Pete LaPaque,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.carlandtracystewart.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/dwlist2.htm |title=British Wrestling DVDs: Classic British Wrestling, Vol. 1 |author=Stewart, Carl and Tracy |date= |work=Carl and Tracy Stewart's British Wrestling DVDs |publisher=CarlandTracyStewart.co.uk |accessdate=2010-05-23}}</ref> [[Mark Rocco|Rollerball Rocco]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.johnlisterwriting.com/itvwrestling/87.html |title=1987 |author=Lister, John |date= |work=ITV wrestling listings |publisher=JohnListerWriting.com |accessdate=2010-05-23}}</ref> Lucky Gordon, "Superstar" Mal Sanders, Dr. Death<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.britishwrestlingarchive.co.uk/1987%20BILLS.htm |title=1987 Bills & Results |author= |date= |work=British Wrestling Results & Bills |publisher=BritishWrestlingArchive.co.uk |accessdate=2010-05-23}}</ref> and [[Skull Murphy]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.britishwrestlingarchive.co.uk/SKULL%20MURPHY.htm |title=Skull Murphy |author= |date= |work=Wrestlers Records |publisher=BritishWrestlingArchive.co.uk |accessdate=2010-05-23}}</ref>

===Retirement===
After his retirement in 1991, following a tour of [[Spain]] and [[Germany]], Cortes opened the Bobby Bold Eagle Wrestling Academy in [[New York City|New York City, New York]]. Among his former students include Billy Firehawk, Tiger Khan-(marlon kalkai),peligro (abe guzman), Panther <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.canoe.ca/Slam/Wrestling/2006/06/29/1659522.html |title=SLAM! Wrestling: Stampede stars remember Tiger Khan |author=Oliver, Greg |date=2006-06-29 |work= |publisher=SLAM! Sports |accessdate=2010-05-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://slam.canoe.ca/Slam/Wrestling/Movies/2008/12/01/7595566.html |title=SLAM! Wrestling: Associate Producer of The Wrestler documents wrestling's killing fields |author=Chhibber, Ranjan |date=2009-01-20 |work= |publisher=SLAM! Sports |accessdate=2010-05-23}}</ref> [[Chris Kanyon]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pro-wrestling.com/displaynews.php?area=4&sid=33844 |title=Kanyon gave all to wrestling |author=Mooneyham, Mike |date=2010-04-18 |work= |publisher=Pro-Wrestling.com |accessdate=2010-05-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.caulifloweralleyclub.org/2010finishes/ |title=2010 Finishes (RIP): Remembering those we have lost in 2010 |author=Cauliflower Alley Club |authorlink=Cauliflower Alley Club |year=2010 |work= |publisher=CauliflowerAlleyClub.org |accessdate=2010-05-23}}</ref> Primo Carnera II and The Power Twins (Larry and David Sontag) as well as [[List of Extreme Championship Wrestling alumni|ECW alumni]] The Dirt Bike Kid, [[Rocco Rock]],and  [[Jason Knight]]

